               <floruit notBefore="1868" notAfter="1917">He was a leading 19th century Semiticist. 
                  He spent most of his adult life in <placeName ref="wd:Q142"/> where he lead a 
                  distinguished career as Orientalist and archaeologist, publishing numerous studies
                  on Semitic languages and epigraphy as well as on the Bible. In <date>1868</date>, 
                  he came to <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop"/> to investigate the situation of 
                  <persName ref="ETH1274Betaes"/> and documented a report on 
                  the circumstance of <persName ref="ETH1274Betaes"/> in those days.
                  In his report, he also  provided a useful information  about <placeName ref="LOC3010Ethiop"/> 
                  during the last years of <persName ref="PRS9430Tewodros"/>.
                  In <date>1879</date>, he began teaching Gǝʿǝz in <placeName ref="wd:Q90"/>.
                  In <date>1893</date>, he founded the Revue sémitique d'épigraphie et d'histoire ancienne
               in which he published much of his work.</floruit>
                  <death when="1917"/>
